sequenceDiagram
    participant Client as Client<br/>(EPP / Gateway)
    participant Sidecar as Routing Sidecar<br/>8000/TCP HTTPS TLS 1.2+
    participant SSRF as SSRF Validator<br/>(in-process)
    participant Prefiller as Remote Prefiller vLLM<br/>varies port HTTP(S)
    participant Decoder as Local Decoder vLLM<br/>8001/TCP HTTP(S)
    participant K8sAPI as Kubernetes API<br/>443/TCP HTTPS

    Note over Client,Decoder: Flow 1: Disaggregated Prefill/Decode (NIXL v2)

    Client->>Sidecar: POST /v1/chat/completions<br/>Header: x-prefiller-host-port=host:port<br/>TLS 1.2+
    Sidecar->>SSRF: Validate prefiller target IP<br/>against InferencePool allowlist
    SSRF-->>Sidecar: Allowed (or 403 Forbidden)

    Note over Sidecar,Prefiller: Clone request: max_tokens=1, stream=false<br/>Add kv_transfer_params.do_remote_decode=true<br/>Set x-request-id=UUID

    Sidecar->>Prefiller: POST /v1/chat/completions<br/>Modified request (prefill phase)<br/>HTTP(S), Optional TLS 1.2+
    Prefiller-->>Sidecar: Response with kv_transfer_params:<br/>remote_block_ids, remote_engine_id,<br/>remote_host, remote_port

    Note over Sidecar,Decoder: Create new request with original params<br/>Attach prefiller kv_transfer_params<br/>Propagate x-request-id

    Sidecar->>Decoder: POST /v1/chat/completions<br/>Original params + KV metadata<br/>HTTP(S)/8001, Optional TLS 1.2+
    Decoder-->>Sidecar: Completion response<br/>(streaming or non-streaming)
    Sidecar-->>Client: Forward response<br/>TLS 1.2+

    Note over Client,Decoder: Flow 2: Direct Decode (No Prefill Header)

    Client->>Sidecar: POST /v1/chat/completions<br/>No x-prefiller-host-port header<br/>TLS 1.2+
    Sidecar->>Decoder: Forward request directly<br/>HTTP(S)/8001, Optional TLS 1.2+
    Decoder-->>Sidecar: Completion response
    Sidecar-->>Client: Forward response<br/>TLS 1.2+

    Note over SSRF,K8sAPI: Flow 3: SSRF Allowlist Update (Background)

    SSRF->>K8sAPI: Watch InferencePool CR<br/>HTTPS/443, ServiceAccount token
    K8sAPI-->>SSRF: InferencePool spec<br/>(label selectors)
    SSRF->>K8sAPI: Watch Pods matching selectors<br/>HTTPS/443, ServiceAccount token
    K8sAPI-->>SSRF: Pod add/update/delete events
    Note over SSRF: Rebuild allowlist from<br/>pod IPs on every event
